        <abstract>
            <p>Position as Curator allows no time for experiment.</p>
            <p>Describes plans for vast new layout of Calcutta Botanic Garden according to natural orders.</p>
            <p>Himalayan and Scottish plants are doing well.</p>
            <p>Hopes to experiment on temperate plants in tropics, to test CD’s views of migration during glacial periods.</p>
            <p>Sends observations on acclimatisation of English cultivated plants.</p> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Leersia</hi> CD sent are growing and fertile.</p> 
        </abstract>
